      • getExactFile

        File getExactFile(K componentId)
        The file for the specified terminology independent component.

        NOTE: file may *NOT* exist if the component specified by its ID does not exist in the taxonomy.

        Parameters:
        componentId - the ID of the component.
        Returns:
        the icon file. May *NOT* exist.

      • getExactFile

        File getExactFile(K componentId,
                  K defaultComponentId)
        The file for the specified terminology independent component.

        NOTE: file may *NOT* exist if the component specified by its ID does not exist in the taxonomy. In this case the supplied defaultComponentId is used to return an icon.

        Parameters:
        componentId - - the ID of the component.
        defaultComponentId - - the default ID.
        Returns:
        the icon file for the componentId or the defaultComponentId.

      • getIconFileName

        @Nullable
String getIconFileName(K componentId)
        Returns with the file name and the extension of physical file for the icon.

        NOTE: may return with null. Clients have to make sure before referencing the file name.

        Parameters:
        componentId - the unique ID of the component.
        Returns:
        the icon file name and the extension.
